The paper deals with communication primitives in multi-hop radio networks, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of radio networks implies a focus on Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which suggests a connection to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses leader election, which is a topic in Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
